To implement this feature, you'll need to call the ChatGPT API as the user types, and then display the suggested completions. You can use the v-autocomplete component from Vuetify for this purpose. Make sure to handle API rate limits and avoid sending too many requests.First, install axios to make API requests from the frontend:bashCopy codenpm install axios
Next, update the frontend/src/components/AddTodo.vue file with the following changes:Import axios and the ChatGPT API key:javascriptCopy codeimport axios from "axios";

const chatGptApiKey = "your_chatgpt_api_key";
Replace your_chatgpt_api_key with your actual API key.Add a search method to fetch completions from the ChatGPT API:javascriptCopy codemethods: {
  // ...
  async search(input, callback) {
    try {
      const response = await axios.post(
        "https://api.openai.com/v1/engines/davinci-codex/completions",
        {
          prompt: `Create a todo item: ${input}`,
          max_tokens: 10,
          n: 5,
          stop: null,
          temperature: 0.7,
        },
        {
          headers: {
            "Content-Type": "application/json",
            Authorization: `Bearer ${chatGptApiKey}`,
          },
        }
      );

      const completions = response.data.choices.map((choice) => {
        return input + choice.text.trim();
      });

      callback(completions);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Error fetching completions:", error);
      callback([]);
    }
  },
},
Replace the v-text-field component with a v-autocomplete component:htmlCopy code<v-autocomplete
  v-model="title"
  :loading="isLoading"
  :search-input.sync="searchText"
  :items="suggestions"
  label="Add a new todo"
  @input="addTodo"
></v-autocomplete>
Add data properties for isLoading, searchText, and suggestions:javascriptCopy codedata() {
  return {
    title: "",
    isLoading: false,
    searchText: "",
    suggestions: [],
  };
},
Add a watcher for searchText to debounce the API calls:javascriptCopy codewatch: {
  searchText(value) {
    if (value && value.length > 2) {
      this.isLoading = true;
      clearTimeout(this.searchDebounce);
      this.searchDebounce = setTimeout(() => {
        this.search(value, (items) => {
          this.suggestions = items;
          this.isLoading = false;
        });
      }, 500);
    } else {
      this.suggestions = [];
    }
  },
},
Now, as the user types a new todo item, the application will fetch text completions from the ChatGPT API and display them as selectable suggestions. Note that you may need to adjust the prompt, parameters, and the ChatGPT API URL according to your specific use case and API version.

